  <DIV>
    
    <B>The Choose Breakfast Challenge - a citywide showdown between the 5 neighborhoods of Millsberry! 
    <BR>
    To earn points for your neighborhood:</B>
    <BR>
    <B>1. Head to the <A HREF='../shop.phtml?shop_id=4'>Millsberry Grocery Store</A> and scope out the Breakfast section</B>, where all the breakfast 
    foods are marked with colored triangles so you'll know which Food Group they belong to:
    <BR>
    Grain <IMG SRC='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/choose_breakfast/orangebox.gif' TITLE='Grain'>
    <BR>
    Fruit <IMG SRC='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/choose_breakfast/redbox.gif' TITLE='Fruit'>
    <BR>
    Dairy <IMG SRC='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/choose_breakfast/bluebox.gif' TITLE='Dairy'>
    <BR>
    Protein <IMG SRC='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/choose_breakfast/purplebox.gif' TITLE='Protein'>.
    <BR>
    <B>2. Buy the items and feed your Millsberry citizen a complete breakfast by including food from 3 
    different Food Groups.</B>
    For example, Try a bowl of cereal <IMG SRC='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/choose_breakfast/orangebox.gif' TITLE='Grain'> with milk <IMG SRC='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/choose_breakfast/bluebox.gif' TITLE='Dairy'> 
    and strawberries <IMG SRC='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/choose_breakfast/redbox.gif' TITLE='Fruit'>.
    <BR>
    <BR>
    * You earn one point for each healthy breakfast food item eaten, up to a maximum of three points per day. 
    <BR>
    * Earn at least 15 points get a specially designed neighborhood t-shirt. 
    <BR>
    <BR>
    
    <B>When:</B>  Will begin on July 14th and run for 14 days 
    <BR>
    <BR>
    <B>The Winner:</B> After the contest ends on July 28th, the winning neighborhood will be awarded a special prize, 
    along with bragging rights. 
    <BR>
    <BR>
    So stock up on cereal, milk, fruit and eggs, and be sure to keep an eye on your neighborhood's progress. 
    <BR>
    Get ready to "Choose Breakfast" - after all, it's the most important meal of the day! 
    
  <DIV>
</DIV>
